processes mentioned above are more important.\n  We also show the non-trivial energy- and angular dependences of the\nflavor-exchange reactions and the inverse muon decay.\n  In the study of the diffusion coefficients from these reactions, we find that\n$\\bar{\\nu}_{\\mu}$ is most affected.\n  These pieces of information are indispensable for numerical computations and\nthe interpretation of results thereof for the proto-neutron star cooling\nparticularly at the very late phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 13 Nov 2022 16:36:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-15"}
