{"id":"2211.07332","submitter":"JianPeng Wang","authors":"Jian-Peng Wang, Qin Qin, Fu-Sheng Yu","title":"CP violation induced by T-odd correlations and its baryonic application","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-ph hep-ex","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The CP asymmetries induced by the T-odd correlations, where T is the time\nreversal, were proposed in literature long time before, but have never been\nestablished in experiments. We provide a first proof in this letter that under\ntwo general conditions, the T-odd CP asymmetries are proportional to the cosine\nof relative strong phases, $\\cos\\delta_{s}$. It improves the understandings of\nthe T-odd CP asymmetries. Furthermore, we propose to measure both the CP\nasymmetries induced by T-odd correlations and their corresponding T-even\ncorrelations, where the latter ones are proportional to the sine of the\nrelative strong phases. In this way, the complementarity of the T-odd and\nT-even CP asymmetries can avoid their suppression by the strong phases with\nsome specific values. We emphasize that this is helpful to search for the CP\nasymmetries in baryon decays, which is crucial to the understanding of the\nbaryon-anti-baryon asymmetry in the universe. In the end, it is clearly shown\nthat the T-odd correlations and their complementarity to the T-even\ncorrelations can be illustrated in the angular distributions in the example\nchain decay.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Nov 2022 13:13:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-15"}
